---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy | OneStopSite 88x31 Button Maker"
  description="Read the privacy policy of OneStopSite. Learn how we handle your data, storage of custom badges, and our 100% client-side privacy commitments."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto pt-0 pb-12 px-4">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-900 pb-8 mb-10 text-center sm:text-left">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-neutral-900 bg-neutral-950 text-xs text-emerald-400 mb-4 font-mono">
        <span class="flex h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 animate-pulse"></span>
        <span>LEGAL POLICY</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4 tracking-tight font-sans">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-base">Last updated: June 18, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-neutral-300 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">1. Overview and Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          At <strong class="text-white font-semibold">OneStopSite</strong>, we take user privacy extremely seriously. We believe in a decentralized, secure, and user-centric web. Because our 88x31 button editor runs <strong class="text-white font-semibold">entirely client-side</strong> in your web browser, we do not upload, collect, or store your custom graphics, images, or layer coordinates on our servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          Since OneStopSite is a client-side application, we do not require account registration or login.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 pl-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
            <span class="text-emerald-500 font-mono select-none mt-1.5">•</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Personal Data:</strong> We do not collect names, email addresses, usernames, or contact details when you use the editor.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
            <span class="text-emerald-500 font-mono select-none mt-1.5">•</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Project & Image Assets:</strong> When you upload a custom background or paste an image from your clipboard into the canvas, this data is processed locally in your browser’s memory. It is never transmitted to our backend.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
            <span class="text-emerald-500 font-mono select-none mt-1.5">•</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Local Storage:</strong> Your templates and active drafts are stored inside your browser's local cache (LocalStorage). This data remains on your machine unless you clear your browser cookies and site cache.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">3. Cookies & Analytical Data</h2>
        <p>
          We may use minimal, privacy-respecting cookies or client analytics utilities to measure generic traffic statistics (such as browser types, referring pages, and page views) to help us optimize the performance of the editor.
        </p>
        <p>
          These analytical utilities do not track your design projects, text layers, keystrokes, or exports. You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time without losing any editor features.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">4. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
        <p>
          Our application imports typography styles from <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Google Fonts</strong>. When your browser requests these font files, Google may collect your IP address in accordance with their standard API policies. We do not control Google's data collections.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">5. User Control & Data Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          You have complete control over your projects. To delete all saved data, templates, and cache stored by OneStopSite, simply click the <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Reset Workspace</strong> button inside the editor preferences, or clear your browser's local storage for this domain.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy periodically to reflect changes in our design editor utility. Any updates will be posted on this page with an updated modification date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">7. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about our privacy practices or the client-side design of the editor, please visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">Contact Page</a> or email us at <code class="bg-neutral-950 px-2 py-0.5 rounded border border-neutral-900 text-neutral-300 font-mono text-sm">maxwrites02@gmail.com</code>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
